    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AlphaWolf
    The AlphaWolf class represents the leader of a wolf pack.
    Animal
    The Animal class represents the base class for all animal entities in the simulation.
    AnimalNest
    Abstract base class for animal nests in the simulation.
    Bear
    The Bear class represents an animal capable of both carnivorous and herbivorous behaviors.
    BerryBush
    Represents a berry bush in the simulation world.
    Carcass
    Represents a carcass in the simulation, which acts as a decaying resource for other entities.
    Carnivorous
    Interface defining the behavior of carnivorous animals in the simulation.
    Functions
     
    Grass
    Represents a patch of grass in the simulation world.
    Herbivorous
    Interface defining the behavior of herbivorous animals in the simulation.
    Main
    Runs the program.
    Mushrooms
    Represents mushrooms in the simulation world.
    Plant
    Represents a generic plant in the simulation world.
    Rabbit
    The Rabbit class is a herbivorous animal in the simulation that engages in activities such as foraging for plants, breeding, and digging/inhabiting rabbit holes.
    RabbitHole
    Represents a rabbit hole in the simulation world.

    Testing class for Plant and the subclasses BerryBush and Grass.
    TestRabbit

    TestWolf
    Testing class for the Wolf Animal.
    Wolf
    The Wolf class represents a wolf in the simulation.
    WolfNest
    Represents a Wolf's hole in the simulation world.
